Linux share mount example:
sudo mkdir -p /mnt/nas
sudo mount -t cifs //nas/public -o username=uname,dom=domain,password=pword /mnt/nas

Rsync command example:
sudo rsync -zWrlpDq --delete /home/user/ws/ws-crx/rex-backup/ /mnt/nas/rex-backup
(z - compress, W - whole file, r - recursive dir, l - links as symlinks, p - preserve permissions, D - special/device files,
q - quite output mode, delete - delete files at the target not present at the source)

